      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: native SwiftUI Crabbox iOS app (crabbox.sh client + on-device/sandbox LLM + islo)",
        "body": "## 🦀 Crabbox for iOS — *a short-lived box for every `run`*, now from your phone\n\nEvolves `mobile/` into a genuinely **native SwiftUI** app — a Crabbox **command center** that warms boxes, runs work across them, and reduces the results, with the **real Crabbox Go CLI compiled into the app** and Apple's on-device LLM on board. No web wrapper, no Expo.\n\n> Provider scope: **islo.dev only.** crabbox.sh is the broker; islo.dev is where the boxes run.\n\n---\n\n### 🧮 Map-Reduce from the phone (the headline)\n\nOne tap fans a computation across N islo sandboxes (**MAP**) and aggregates on the phone (**REDUCE**). Live demo — `Σ(1…1000)` + min/max across **3 islo sandboxes**:\n\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zozo123/crabbox/codex/ios-mobile-app/mobile/docs/screenshots/mapreduce-demo.gif\" width=\"280\">\n\n```\n$ map-reduce  Σ(1…1000)  over 3 islo sandbox(es)\n  [probe] crabbox-mapreduce-demo-{0,1,2} ✓ live\n  [map]   demo-2 → sum=55611   min=1   max=333     (1…333)\n  [map]   demo-0 → sum=166500  min=334 max=666     (334…666)\n  [map]   demo-1 → sum=278389  min=667 max=1000    (667…1000)\n  [reduce] Σ = 55611 + 166500 + 278389 = 500500 · min 1 · max 1000   ✅\n```\n\nVerified live against `api.islo.dev`. The runner probes the targets, **re-shards across only the live boxes** (so the total is always correct), runs each shard via `IsloClient.exec` in parallel, and reduces on-device. A 4-box run reduces `31375 + 93875 + 156375 + 218875 = 500500` the same way.\n\n---\n\n### ✨ Everything it does\n\n| | Use case | Where |\n|---|---|---|\n| 🧮 | **Map-reduce / command center** — shard work across N islo boxes, reduce on the phone | Run |\n| 🖥️ | **Run a Crabbox command on islo** — embedded Go core runs `crabbox run --provider islo …` **in-process** | Run |\n| 📦 | **Sandbox lifecycle** — list / pause / resume / delete islo boxes | Sandboxes |\n| 🔗 | **crabbox.sh as broker** — coordinator provisions & runs on islo-backed workspaces | Run / Sandboxes |\n| 🧠 | **LLM** — Apple **Foundation Models** on-device (verified on an iPhone 16) + Ollama on a leased islo box | Assistant |\n| 🌐 | **Portal** — native WebView of **crabbox.sh** | Portal |\n| 🔐 | **Secrets in the Keychain** | Settings |\n\n### 📱 Screens\n\n| Run — command center | Sandboxes — live islo leases |\n|:--:|:--:|\n| <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zozo123/crabbox/codex/ios-mobile-app/mobile/docs/screenshots/01-run.png\" width=\"240\"> | <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zozo123/crabbox/codex/ios-mobile-app/mobile/docs/screenshots/02-sandboxes.png\" width=\"240\"> |\n| **Assistant — on-device LLM** | **Portal — live crabbox.sh** |\n| <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zozo123/crabbox/codex/ios-mobile-app/mobile/docs/screenshots/03-assistant.png\" width=\"240\"> | <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zozo123/crabbox/codex/ios-mobile-app/mobile/docs/screenshots/04-portal.png\" width=\"240\"> |\n\n---\n\n### 🏗️ How the Go core runs on iOS\n\niOS can't spawn a separate `crabbox` binary, so the Go engine is compiled into the app as a **`-buildmode=c-archive` static library** (`CrabboxMobile`) and called via a tiny C/Swift bridge:\n\n```\nSwift ──JSON──▶ CrabboxMobileRun(*C.char) ──▶ cli.App{}.Run(ctx, args)   // the real internal/cli\n      ◀─JSON── {exitCode, stdout, stderr}      + mobile-safe islo provider (HTTPS to islo.dev)\n```\n\n**CrabboxKit** is the pure, testable Swift core (`IsloClient`, `CoordinatorClient`, provisioners, LLM engines) — builds on macOS **and** Linux. **App** is the SwiftUI surface (Run / Sandboxes / Assistant / Portal) in a polished dark Crabbox theme.\n\n### ✅ Validated end-to-end\n- **Builds, installs, and runs on a physical iPhone 16 (iOS 26.5)** and the **iOS 17 simulator** — Go core links on both (device link needs `-lresolv`; the iOS SDK's `libresolv.9.tbd` exports the `res_9_*` symbols Go uses).\n- **Map-reduce over real islo sandboxes → 500500** (above).\n- Apple on-device LLM (Foundation Models) confirmed working on the iPhone 16.\n- `swift build` · `go build ./mobile/go/crabboxmobile` · `swift run crabbox-sim` (18 scenarios, 0 invariant violations).\n\n### 🔧 Also in this revision\n- **islo auth hardening**: `IsloClient` retries once on HTTP 401 (re-exchanges the API key) so a session JWT expiring/rotating mid-run doesn't fail the map-reduce.\n- **LLM readiness**: a launched sandbox engine isn't offered for chat until Ollama is actually serving (poll `isReady()` before registering).\n- Writable `XDG_STATE_HOME`/`HOME` for the Go core's lease-claim system in the iOS sandbox.\n- Sandbox targeting via `--slug` (correct `run` flag).\n- Fixed a Portal crash on malformed `mailto:`/`tel:` URLs.\n- **UI polish**: refined palette + brighter mint, 8-pt spacing, haptics, terminal styling, springy buttons; **chat keyboard dismissal** (swipe, tap, Done toolbar, dismiss-on-send).\n\n### 📦 Install on a device\n```sh\ncd mobile\nDEVELOPMENT_TEAM=XXXXXXXXXX ./scripts/install-on-device.sh\n```\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
